#ideologies
Chauvinism: belief in superiority of own group, excessive nationalism
Nepotism: granting advantage to relatives/friends
Misogyny: hatred of women
Ableism: social prejudice against people with disabilities (less valuable)
Feminism: gender equality; right to vote, education and work; legal abortions, domestic violence
Eugenics: improvement of human genetic quality by excluding inferior groups (selective breeding)
Capitalism: private ownership, operation for profit, property rights, wage labor
Socialism: social ownership
- Marxism
- Communism: absence of private ownership and money
Fascism: dictatorship, militarism
- Nazism: dictatorship, anti-communism, white supremacy, eugenics
Militarism: strong army, aggressive expansion
Imperialism: power over foreign nation, empire
Colonialism: group of people superior to other people, resource extraction
Mercantilism: maximize export and minimize import
Nationalism: sovereign nation-states, self determination
Liberalism: individual rights and freedoms, equality, free market
Irredentism: desire to annex territory of another state (ethnic/historical reasons)

#systems
meritocracy: based on ability
democracy: elections, freedoms
- direct: people decide
- representative: elected officials decide on behalf of people
monarchy: term for life, often hereditary
- absolute
- constitutional
authoritarianism: limiting political plurality
- totalitarian
- authocratic
- oligarchic

#elections
Condorcet winner: candidate that would win against all other candidates, if there were only two candidates
wasted vote: vote not helping to elect a candidate
plurality: majority of votes can be wasted 
- single-member plurality / first past the post (one winner)
- plurality at large (multiple winners)
majority: minority is unrepresented
- two-round / runoff (second round with 2 candidates only)
- ranked choice / preferential / instant-runoff (candidates are ordered)
proportional
- single transferable vote (candidates are ordered, multiple winners)
- party-list proportional (seats per party by votes)

