#Grundgesetz (Deutschland)
Basic rights
1: human dignity
2: personal freedom
3: equality before law
4: freedom of faith
5: freedom of speech
6: marriage and family
7: public school system
8: freedom of assembly
9: freedom of societies
10: privacy of correspondence
11: freedom of movement
12: freedom of occupation
12a: compulsory military/civilian service
13: inviolability of home (except emergency)
14: property rights
15: nationalisation
16: citizenship
16a: right of asylum
17: right of petition
18: loss of rights
19: restriction of rights

#Constitution (USA)
Bill of Rights
1: freedom of faith and speech, right of assembly and petition
2: right to own and bear arms for defense
3: housing soldiers can not be forced
4: no search without warrant or probable cause
5: protection against double jeopardy and self-incrimination
6: right of jury trial in criminal cases
7: right of jury trial in federal civil cases
8: no excessive bail, no unusual or cruel punishment
9: no denial of other rights
10: government power is limited by constitution 
Other Amendments
11: state sovereign immunity
13: abolition of slavery
